<heading id="5A24A609FF97394FE971C44EFBC058A1" box="[576,1087,892,919]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="2">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE9A2C44FFBC058A1" authority="Frizzell &amp; Dante, 1965" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Dante" authorityYear="1965" box="[659,1087,892,919]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE9A2C44FFCD658A1" bold="true" box="[659,809,892,919]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Preophidion</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF97394FE801C44FFBC058A1" author="Frizzell &amp; Dante" box="[816,1087,892,919]" firstAuthor="Frizzell" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="687 - 718" refId="ref53957" refString="Frizzell D. L. &amp; Dante J. H. 1965. Otoliths of some early Cenozoic fishes of the Gulf Coast. Journal of Paleontology 39: 687 - 718." type="journal article" year="1965">Frizzell &amp; Dante, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF97394FEBD2C48DFC645E75" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF97394FEBD2C48DFEAA58EE" blockId="57.[227,341,958,984]" box="[227,341,958,984]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<heading id="5A24A609FF97394FEBD2C48DFEAA58EE" bold="true" box="[227,341,958,984]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEBD2C48DFEAA58EE" bold="true" box="[227,341,958,984]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF97394FEBD2C4DFFC645E75" blockId="57.[227,1437,1004,1348]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEBD2C4DFFE8A5F30" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Dante" authorityYear="1965" box="[227,373,1004,1030]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEBD2C4DFFE8A5F30" box="[227,373,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Preophidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extinct genus with otoliths resembling those of the extant 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEFB1C4DFFB1E5F30" box="[1152,1249,1004,1030]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Sirembo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEFB1C4DFFB1E5F30" box="[1152,1249,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Sirembo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We here place 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEBD2C323FDE75F1C" authority="(Koken, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[227,536,1039,1066]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elevatus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEBD2C323FE9F5F1F" box="[227,352,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. elevatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF97394FEA40C33CFDF15F1C" author="Koken" box="[369,526,1039,1066]" firstAuthor="Koken" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="274 - 305" refId="ref54599" refString="Koken E. 1888. Neue Untersuchungen an tertiaren Fisch-Otolithen. Zeitschrift der deutschen geologischen Gesellschaft 40: 274 - 305." type="journal article" year="1888">Koken, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE914C323FCB35F1C" authority="(Muller, 1999)" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[549,844,1039,1066]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="granus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE914C323FD6B5F1F" box="[549,660,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. granus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF97394FE994C33CFCBC5F1C" author="Muller" box="[677,835,1039,1066]" firstAuthor="Muller" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref55491" refString="Muller A. 1999. Ichthyofaunen aus dem atlantischen Tertiar der USA. Leipziger Geowissenschaften 9 / 10: 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1999">Müller, 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE8BAC323FAB55F1C" authority="(Dante &amp; Frizzell, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[907,1354,1039,1066]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petropolis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE8BAC323FBE05F1F" box="[907,1055,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">P. petropolis</emphasis>
(Dante &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF97394FEFACC33CFABD5F1C" author="Frizzell D. L." box="[1181,1346,1039,1066]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="85 - 110" refId="ref53928" refString="Frizzell D. L. 1965. Otolith-based genera and lineages of fossil bonefishes (Clupeiformes, Albulidae). Senckenbergiana Lethaea 46 a: 85 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1965">Frizzell, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in this genus. “ 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEA72C300FE325F7B" authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" box="[323,461,1075,1101]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Neobythites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEA72C300FE325F7B" box="[323,461,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Neobythites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEAD0C307FDCE5F7B" box="[481,561,1076,1101]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEAD0C307FDCE5F7B" box="[481,561,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE946C307FD745F7B" box="[631,651,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">N</emphasis>
.” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE997C307FD015F7B" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[678,766,1076,1101]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Phycidae" genus="Symmetrosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stintoni">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE997C307FD015F7B" box="[678,766,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">stintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were initially also assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEF56C300FB065F7B" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Dante" authorityYear="1965" box="[1127,1273,1075,1101]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEF56C300FB065F7B" box="[1127,1273,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Preophidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF97394FEE14C300FE7D5F47" author="Frizzell &amp; Dante" firstAuthor="Frizzell" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="687 - 718" refId="ref53957" refString="Frizzell D. L. &amp; Dante J. H. 1965. Otoliths of some early Cenozoic fishes of the Gulf Coast. Journal of Paleontology 39: 687 - 718." type="journal article" year="1965">Frizzell &amp; Dante (1965)</bibRefCitation>
, and this was followed as such in 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF97394FE827C365FBE65F46" author="Ebersole" box="[790,1049,1110,1136]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ebersole" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" refId="ref53603" refString="Ebersole J. A., Cicimurri D. J. &amp; Stringer G. L. 2019. Taxonomy and biostratigraphy of the elasmobranchs and bony fishes (Chondrichthyes and Osteichthyes) of the lower - to - middle Eocene (Ypresian to Bartonian) Claiborne Group in Alabama, USA, including an analysis of otoliths. European Journal of" type="book" year="2019">
Ebersole 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE8B7C364FC465F46" box="[902,953,1110,1136]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, but here we reassign the former two species to the 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEA86C34AFD8A5FA5" authorityName="Schwarzhans" authorityYear="1981" box="[439,629,1145,1171]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Phycidae" genus="Symmetrosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEA86C34AFD8A5FA5" box="[439,629,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Symmetrosulcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above). The most significant distinctive feature between otoliths of 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEA34C3AFFE3B5F80" box="[261,452,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Symmetrusulcus</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE933C3AFFD6B5F80" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Dante" authorityYear="1965" box="[514,660,1180,1206]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE933C3AFFD6B5F80" box="[514,660,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Preophidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists in the cleavage between the ostial and caudal collicula, which is vertical and short in otoliths of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE98EC38CFC825FEF" authorityName="Schwarzhans" authorityYear="1981" box="[703,893,1215,1241]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Phycidae" genus="Symmetrosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE98EC38CFC825FEF" box="[703,893,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Symmetrosulcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas it is more oblique and inclined in an anterodorsal-posteroventral direction in the more 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FE80BC3D0FC645FCB" box="[826,923,1251,1277]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Sirembo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FE80BC3D0FC645FCB" box="[826,923,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Sirembo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like otoliths of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEF50C3D0FB0C5FCB" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Dante" authorityYear="1965" box="[1121,1267,1251,1277]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Preophidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEF50C3D0FB0C5FCB" box="[1121,1267,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Preophidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF97394FEBD5C235FEBC5E16" box="[228,323,1286,1312]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Sirembo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF97394FEBD5C235FEBC5E16" box="[228,323,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Sirembo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like otoliths usually have a wider sulcus, a sharply restricted collum on the crista inferior, a more considerable thickness and a more convex inner face.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
